  "prompt": "What is digital PR?",
  "response": "Digital PR is a modern public relations strategy that uses online channels and digital platforms to build brand awareness, manage reputation, and create positive publicity. Key aspects include:\n\n1. Key components:\n- Online media relations\n- Content marketing\n- Social media engagement\n- Influencer partnerships\n- SEO-driven publicity\n- Press release distribution\n- Online reputation management\n\n2. Primary goals:\n- Increase brand visibility\n- Generate online coverage\n- Build high-quality backlinks\n- Improve search engine rankings\n- Enhance digital brand reputation\n\n3. Typical tactics:\n- Creating shareable content\n- Writing guest blog posts\n- Engaging with online journalists\n- Developing digital press kits\n- Managing social media communication\n- Securing online media mentions\n- Leveraging digital storytelling\n\n4. Measurement methods:\n- Website traffic\n- Social media engagement\n- Domain authority\n- Backlink quality\n- Online brand mentions\n- Search engine rankings\n\n5. Differences from traditional PR:\n- Primarily digital platforms\n- More measurable results\n- Faster communication\n- Global reach\n- Interactive communication\n- Lower cost\n- Real-time feedback\n\nDigital PR aims to create meaningful online connections and positive digital brand perception through strategic digital communication and content strategies.",
